                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/8238: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-09T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 9, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Your letter July 7 to Briggs regarding mediation in Spain.<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d184fn82">Not printed; but see memorandum dated July 7, <ref
                            target="#pg_225">p. 225</ref>.</note> You may informally advise the
                    Secretary of State that our policy of noninterference in the Spanish situation
                    would preclude our participation in any such action as that proposed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
